WorkItem.Description:
Hello Everyone,

I am trying to export data directly from the database to a downloadable Excel spreadsheet, the formatting is showing. However, the data is not displaying. Can anyone help me? Also, when opening the spreadsheet it gives me the message "We found a problem with some content in 'FileName'. Do you want us to try to recover..." See code and spreadsheet attached.

Thanks

Comments.Message: All the echos were commented it out in the file, so they were not the problem.

Don't echo/print any output at all from your PHP script when sending a download to the browser

** Closed by MarkBaker 8/21/2014 12:48 PM

I can see from the file that you posted there is a spurious extra line after your closing `?>`.... that's output.... that's why all the PHPExcel files don't have any terminating `?>`, to guarantee that the library code can never introduce spurious output
